subSubSection.paragraph:
Carapace longer than broad (
Fig. 13
). Without eyes or eye-spots. Anterior margin moderately prominent medially, epistome blunt and almost indistinguishable, with some tiny denticles not exceeding the anterior margin (
Fig. 14
). Chaetotaxy: 20 setae, formula 4 : 4 : 6 : 6 . Five microlyrifissures on ocular zone, two between median and posterior zones.

Coxal area. Manducatory process with 3 setae. Anterior process of coxa I with simple tooth shape, long and apically pointed; medial process straight with a few denticles (
Fig. 15
). Pedipalpal coxa with 7 setae, pedal coxa I with 6 , II: 3–4 , III: 3–4 , IV: 6 .

Chelicerae (
Figs 16–17
). Palm with 6 setae; subgaleal seta 0.65 from base of movable finger. Galea short (length 0.03 mm ), pointed and simple. Fixed finger with 6 small, blunt, distal denticles, resembling protuberances, and 10 normal teeth, 4 basal ones larger than the others; movable finger with 17 teeth, one large and blunt subdistal tooth, the others medium or small, dental row ending just proximad of subgaleal seta. Rallum with 8 blades, all unilaterally pinnate on anterior face, the basal one about half length of others. Serrula exterior with 31 blades, serrula interior 25 blades.

